 was identified by the bank=E2=80=99s
security systems as a =E2=80=9Crisky=E2=80=9D transaction. I asked what mad=
e this transaction =E2=80=9Crisky=E2=80=9D since I was sending my own money=
 to someone I had been doing business with through Chase for 20 years. =E2=
=80=9CAny transaction that you make, not just a wire transfer, will be subj=
ect to certain fraud prevention reviews and risk reviews,=E2=80=9D he said.=
 =E2=80=9CAnd this will be done as per the bank&#39;s fraud prevention poli=
cy and risk policy.=E2=80=9D He reiterated that this particular wire transf=
er was =E2=80=9Cidentified=E2=80=9D as =E2=80=9Ca risky payment, and based =
on this risk review, our systems have automatically declined this transacti=
on.=E2=80=9D He said there was nothing he could do to rectify the situation=
 after the system rejected the wire transfer the third time. =E2=80=9CThis =
is a situation, unfortunately, which cannot be resolved,=E2=80=9D he said.<=
br/><br/>I wrote a check and put it in the mail. I=E2=80=99ve never bought =
