lCRVJTKyUyODclMkYxNCUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9RHJ5K1Bvd2RlcistK1NVQ=
lNDUklCRVJTKyUyODYlMkYzMCUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25c=
dTAwMjZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJ=
kMTJhIiwiaW50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjo5NTY5MDR9/6=
f8bd6e2e394a6fecc6cbfd229229b330adcaa42cb8d84bf34934d3518950173" style=3D"c=
olor:#d40000;text-decoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">reporting=
</a></u> from Deadline.) Anyone just making an offer for NAI will not get t=
he special committee to change its recommendation on the Ellison/RedBird de=
al, unless the offer to the B shareholders exceeds $15 a share, which is wh=
at it will take for someone to top Ellison/RedBird. (In the unlikely event =
that
happens, the Ellisons and <b>Gerry Cardinale</b> will receive a $400 millio=
n breakup fee.) The only hope for the B shareholders, as well as the non-Re=
dstone A shareholders, such as the long-suffering <b>Mario Gabelli</b>, is =
for the Sony/Apollo deal to somehow be resurrected and sweetened.<br/></td>
